name: pdfplumber
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "pdfplumber" %}
{% set version = "0.7.3" %}


package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/pdfplumber-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 3b17536606585e1f0df99264aee06201812918aa6ca3a5d3bd520501226d19cc

build:
  number: 0
  entry_points:
    - pdfplumber = pdfplumber.cli:main
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv
  noarch: python

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python >=3.6.*
  run:
    - pdfminer.six ==20220524
    - pillow >=9.1
    - python >=3.6.*
    - wand >=0.6.7

test:
  imports:
    - pdfplumber
  commands:
    - pip check
    - pdfplumber --help
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: https://github.com/jsvine/pdfplumber
  summary: Plumb a PDF for detailed information about each char, rectangle, and line.
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE.txt

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - melonhead901
